9a2c7e49-719a-5e74-aa54-9d202d5d55c2.title: Common registers and commands
9a2c7e49-719a-5e74-aa54-9d202d5d55c2.description:

These are defined in ranges separate from the per-service ones.
No service actually derives from this file, but services can include packets
defined here.
Their code is listed as say `@ intensity` and not `@ 0x01` (the spectool enforces that).

5cd9eaa9-333a-5bc8-a62b-3f984642b99a.title: Microbit-LED
5cd9eaa9-333a-5bc8-a62b-3f984642b99a.description: The expansion board integrates 24 programmable RGB lights and microphones, and you can control the on-board RGB lights by the microphone.

2a7e95b4-72fc-579c-8549-a961e62b4249.title: Tiny-Bit
2a7e95b4-72fc-579c-8549-a961e62b4249.description: Tiny:bit is a robotic car for the micro:bit education market. It is compact, easy to assemble, and easy to move in tight spaces. The Tiny:bit smart car is based on the micro:bit development board design and uses the online code programming of MakeCode Editor. Rich sensor applications allow Tiny:bit for easy interaction. The Tiny:bit smart car has a set of alligator clips on the rear that can be creative and expand.

c1c5e586-350f-5610-93c1-b441a7c2283d.title: Acidity
c1c5e586-350f-5610-93c1-b441a7c2283d.description: A sensor measuring water acidity, commonly called pH.

7c139374-de3c-505e-b5ab-5be44eea8c75.title: FeatherS2 ESP32-S2
7c139374-de3c-505e-b5ab-5be44eea8c75.description: The full-featured ESP32-S2 based development board in a Feather format from Unexpected Maker. The FeatherS2 is a power house, fully souped up with 16 MB of Flash memory (for firmware and file storage) and 8 MB of QSPI-based external PSRAM so you can have massive storage buffers.

a42ee426-4b8c-5156-8cf0-9db3554e5a86.title: Air Pressure
a42ee426-4b8c-5156-8cf0-9db3554e5a86.description: A sensor measuring air pressure of outside environment.

0031b9d7-da2c-5759-962c-8c93fad11377.title: B-L475E-IOT01A DeviceScript
0031b9d7-da2c-5759-962c-8c93fad11377.description: B-L475E-IOT01A running Jacdac firmware accessing built-in sensors and DeviceScript. Built with AzureRTOS.

dc5ad79f-2783-587f-a00a-01f6da6ce37d.title: Air Quality Index
dc5ad79f-2783-587f-a00a-01f6da6ce37d.description:
The Air Quality Index is a measure of how clean or polluted air is. From min, good quality, to high, low quality.
The range of AQI may vary between countries (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Air_quality_index).

46a4cb9c-e2ca-55db-bd10-6d3ee886de65.title: gamer:bit
46a4cb9c-e2ca-55db-bd10-6d3ee886de65.description: The SparkFun gamer:bit is a fun-filled "carrier" board for the micro:bit that, when combined with the micro:bit, provides you with a fully functional game system. Designed in a similar form factor to the classic Nintendo NES controller, the gamer:bit is equipped with a four-direction "D-pad" on the left side of the board and two action buttons on the right side of the board. The two push buttons on the micro:bit in the center function as start and select.

1a57487e-8b83-5a7c-ab66-6ad56ef454df.title: Arcade Gamepad
1a57487e-8b83-5a7c-ab66-6ad56ef454df.description:
This service is deprecated in favor of `gamepad` (although it is currently used by the micro:bit Arcade smart shield).
A gamepad with direction and action buttons for one player.
If a device has multiple controllers, it should have multiple gamepad services, using consecutive service identifiers.

7dc7669a-95e7-506c-b9d9-71c0a6206981.title: Grove-16x2 LCD
7dc7669a-95e7-506c-b9d9-71c0a6206981.description: Seeedstudio Grove - 16 x 2 LCD is a I2C LCD display. 16x2 means two lines and each line has 16 columns, 32 characters in total.

fe8345ca-b298-56fa-8175-3c449162aa37.title: Arcade Sound
fe8345ca-b298-56fa-8175-3c449162aa37.description:
A sound playing device.

This is typically run over an SPI connection, not regular single-wire Jacdac.

62bd4420-136a-5ac2-b422-49b741f05779.title: Relay
62bd4420-136a-5ac2-b422-49b741f05779.description: The Grove-Relay module is a digital normally-open switch. Through it, you can control circuit of high voltage with low voltage, 3.3-5V on the controller. There is an indicator LED on the board, which will light up when the controlled terminals get closed.

16e5a6f1-6dd9-5e85-bf31-d1bee618c924.title: Barcode reader
16e5a6f1-6dd9-5e85-bf31-d1bee618c924.description: A device that reads various barcodes, like QR codes. For the web, see [BarcodeDetector](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/BarcodeDetector).

c6bbc2c1-4956-5d37-83b8-54df82e25863.title: Soil Moisture
c6bbc2c1-4956-5d37-83b8-54df82e25863.description: Soil Moisture Sensor can measure soil moisture for plants. The soil moisture sensor consists of two probes that allow the current to pass through the soil and then obtain resistance values to measure soil moisture content.

94a7d4cd-39d3-5f47-8548-b7e23852d9ab.title: bit:radio
94a7d4cd-39d3-5f47-8548-b7e23852d9ab.description: Support for sending and receiving packets using the [Bit Radio protocol](https://github.com/microsoft/pxt-common-packages/blob/master/libs/radio/docs/reference/radio.md), typically used between micro:bit devices.

d3cf0f64-4c73-5dc5-8157-20338d878834.title: Ultrasonic Distance Sensor
d3cf0f64-4c73-5dc5-8157-20338d878834.description: This Grove - Ultrasonic ranger is a non-contact distance measurement module which works at 40KHz. When we provide a pulse trigger signal with more than 10uS through signal pin, the Grove_Ultrasonic_Ranger will issue 8 cycles of 40kHz cycle level and detect the echo. The pulse width of the echo signal is proportional to the measured distance.

7c87e711-d449-557d-aec4-4c6f640b9028.title: Bootloader
7c87e711-d449-557d-aec4-4c6f640b9028.description:
Allows flashing (reprogramming) devices over Jacdac.

This is typically implemented by having a separate _bootloader_ mode, as opposed to _application_ mode
on the module to be flashed.
The bootloader mode is entered on every device reset, for about 300ms.
The bootloader will generally not announce itself, until it gets some command.
Once it gets the command, it will stay in application mode.

Typically, you ask the module (in application mode) to reset, while sending broadcast
`info` commands to all bootloaders every 100ms or so.
Alternatively, you ask the the user to disconnect and re-connect the module, while
broadcasting `info` commands.
The second method works even if the application is damaged (eg., due to an aborted flash).

When device is in bootloader mode, the device ID may change compared to application mode,
by flipping the first bit in the first byte of the device identifier.

99e4f648-9c58-5b88-829e-cd1dfce6af20.title: XIAO ESP32C3
99e4f648-9c58-5b88-829e-cd1dfce6af20.description: A tiny dev-board with ESP32-C3 from Seeed.

c3f53d74-77f8-5c0c-af74-bf458c93fcbc.title: Braille display
c3f53d74-77f8-5c0c-af74-bf458c93fcbc.description: A Braille pattern display module. This module display [unicode braille patterns](https://www.unicode.org/charts/PDF/U2800.pdf), country specific encoding have to be implemented by the clients.

161f856f-3f55-55aa-97a6-321f2e400770.title: MakerBit
161f856f-3f55-55aa-97a6-321f2e400770.description: The MakerBit board provides simple and efficient connections to the features of the BBC micro:bit. Easily and quickly add lights and touch sensors to school projects, models and art installations. There are enough connecting wires and LEDs for one project. The MakerBit can control a maximum of 12 LEDs and 12 touch sensors in any one project.

1d8fc87d-12f3-56ba-8763-914cabf4335a.title: Bridge
1d8fc87d-12f3-56ba-8763-914cabf4335a.description: Indicates that the device acts as a bridge to the Jacdac bus.

0f826e4c-7a03-58da-901d-97ee83902ae7.title: Pico
0f826e4c-7a03-58da-901d-97ee83902ae7.description: Raspberry Pi Pico is a low-cost, high-performance microcontroller board with flexible digital interfaces.

e3f3ed97-54aa-508f-b845-b741bdc70578.title: Button
e3f3ed97-54aa-508f-b845-b741bdc70578.description: A push-button, which returns to inactive position when not operated anymore.

4b605f7f-2b8f-5b42-be92-6dcc182a7d66.title: Pico W
4b605f7f-2b8f-5b42-be92-6dcc182a7d66.description: Raspberry Pi Pico is a low-cost, high-performance microcontroller board with flexible digital interfaces. Raspberry Pi Pico W adds on-board single-band 2.4GHz wireless interfaces (802.11n) using the Infineon CYW43439 while retaining the Pico form factor.

a96a62e2-3843-5185-ba0b-ce3396e58097.title: micro:bit V2
a96a62e2-3843-5185-ba0b-ce3396e58097.description: The new micro:bit V2 has a built-in microphone and speaker to allow sound-sensing and sound-making without the need to attach another device. It also introduces capacitive touch sensing, a power-saving mode and more computing power for the classroom.

88b5ae02-7352-56da-9b38-b8971ed46c22.title: Capacitive Button
88b5ae02-7352-56da-9b38-b8971ed46c22.description: A configuration service for a capacitive push-button.

8d9dfd96-46f6-5e7d-b80a-06b74ef11c9b.title: Character Screen
8d9dfd96-46f6-5e7d-b80a-06b74ef11c9b.description: A screen that displays characters, typically a LCD/OLED character screen.

b5ded1a4-b6a9-5aed-adf1-5499f245c9f6.title: Cardputer
b5ded1a4-b6a9-5aed-adf1-5499f245c9f6.description: Cardputer is a card-sized portable computer that is perfect for engineers. At the heart of Cardputer is the M5StampS3, a mini development board based on the ESP32-S3 chip. Cardputer features a powerful dual-core processor, supports Wi-Fi functionality and integrates various peripherals and sensors, making it ideal for rapid functional verification, industrial control and home automation systems.

1961da73-5473-55ae-9ea6-afd5524b9550.title: Cloud Adapter
1961da73-5473-55ae-9ea6-afd5524b9550.description:
Supports cloud connections to upload and download data.
Note that `f64` values following a label are not necessarily aligned.

1f3f861e-20b7-5909-936b-1db43ddce403.title: Cloud Configuration
1f3f861e-20b7-5909-936b-1db43ddce403.description: Connection and diagnostics information about the cloud connection.

e12239d4-f0fd-58d5-82b0-d520f4005d77.title: Calliogamer
e12239d4-f0fd-58d5-82b0-d520f4005d77.description:
The CallioGamer can easyly plugged under your calliope mini and provides eight gamepad buttons to control whatever you want.
Only a male 2x15 pin header and 8 tactile switches are needed to built your own CallioGamer!

2077a73d-fe61-57e4-a9bf-45a06319b383.title: CODAL Message Bus
2077a73d-fe61-57e4-a9bf-45a06319b383.description:
A service that uses the [CODAL message bus](https://lancaster-university.github.io/microbit-docs/ubit/messageBus/) to send and receive small messages.

You can find known values for `source` in [CODAL repository](https://github.com/lancaster-university/codal-core/blob/master/inc/core/CodalComponent.h)
In MakeCode, you can listen for custom `source`, `value` values using [control.onEvent](https://makecode.microbit.org/reference/control/on-event].

976dea58-4d46-5571-bbc8-93f990c98eed.title: Accelerometer
976dea58-4d46-5571-bbc8-93f990c98eed.description: Accelerometer sensors are devices used to measure acceleration or motion.

4c10fea8-c7dc-543e-898c-45f70a5ad6e9.title: AgileWhisker Keyboard Elite60
4c10fea8-c7dc-543e-898c-45f70a5ad6e9.description: This is the first mechanical keyboard in the Jacdac system, featuring a 60% layout, a rotary encoder, RGB LED lighting, and two Jacdac interfaces. It is powered by the RP2040 microcontroller.

509bc146-7a0d-5665-9fd5-6bbb399e3af3.title: Compass
509bc146-7a0d-5665-9fd5-6bbb399e3af3.description: A sensor that measures the heading.

f80f5cdb-1769-5ca2-91c0-f10b1c4b35ad.title: AgileWhisker Numeric Keypad
f80f5cdb-1769-5ca2-91c0-f10b1c4b35ad.description: This is the first numeric keypad in the Jacdac system, featuring an OLED screen, a rotary encoder, RGB LED lighting, and one Jacdac interface. It is powered by the RP2040 microcontroller.

e4ce419b-b66c-548e-996f-e91a0c44a3a0.title: Control
e4ce419b-b66c-548e-996f-e91a0c44a3a0.description:
Control service is always service index `0`.
It handles actions common to all services on a device.

Note: some of the optional features (including `flood_ping`, `mcu_temperature`, and all string registers)
are not implemented in `8bit` version.

ef791dfd-1583-55d2-a4e7-4b67ae4e796f.title: AW Agent
ef791dfd-1583-55d2-a4e7-4b67ae4e796f.description: AW Agent, short for AgileWhisker Agent, is a small software for PC computers that is designed to be used in conjunction with AgileWhisker Keyboard Elite60 and other keyboards. It is an open-source software. It functions as a virtual hardware within the jacdac ecosystem. It incorporates MQTT services to retrieve hardware information from the computer and trigger computer events, among other functionalities.

4905ee7e-d863-5b2f-b496-4cc9651c3436.title: Dashboard
4905ee7e-d863-5b2f-b496-4cc9651c3436.description: Device that interacts, configure or inspects with the services on the bus. While a dashboard is on the bus, heuristics like device reset should be disabled.

792b5ca0-aff2-52c2-947c-594cd6cca6c1.title: DuckyBot Kit
792b5ca0-aff2-52c2-947c-594cd6cca6c1.description: Dive into the enchanting world of robotics with DuckyBot, a delightful cardboard robot shaped like a cheerful yellow duck. Engineered around the groundbreaking Jacdac Elite Module Suite, DuckyBot offers young learners a quirky and entertaining gateway into the vast realm of electronics and robotics, integrating seamlessly with Microbit and Makecode platforms.

ee9f5981-143d-5cd7-9ab1-2262062b61a6.title: DC Current Measurement
ee9f5981-143d-5cd7-9ab1-2262062b61a6.description: A service that reports a current measurement.

45f07701-d082-5a82-bd37-fdf3bed06834.title: Env Sensor
45f07701-d082-5a82-bd37-fdf3bed06834.description: Env Sensor is a device used to measure both the temperature and humidity of the surrounding environment.

cac12bac-c885-5535-a765-73d6675f9856.title: DC Voltage Measurement
cac12bac-c885-5535-a765-73d6675f9856.description: A service that reports a voltage measurement.

ef62b7f4-16fb-5f89-9582-60fee559b252.title: Grape:bit
ef62b7f4-16fb-5f89-9582-60fee559b252.description: Grape:bit is a programming main control board mainly for the second to third grade information technology learning and institutional teaching. Its core is the ESP32, which has the characteristics of high performance, wireless communication, and graphical programming.

f12be37f-20f8-543d-9b14-e9dacaaa3800.title: DeviceScript Condition
f12be37f-20f8-543d-9b14-e9dacaaa3800.description:
Conditions are synthetic services used to synchronize threads of executions of a DeviceScript VM.
**This is no longer used**.

e8f79697-44d2-5969-9117-4a5ab4509a20.title: Haptic Output
e8f79697-44d2-5969-9117-4a5ab4509a20.description: The Haptic Output module is essentially a vibration motor that can be used to provide haptic feedback in electronic devices.

d2ff59e3-0e1f-57ed-8d7c-5090e6833f70.title: DeviceScript Debugger
d2ff59e3-0e1f-57ed-8d7c-5090e6833f70.description: Allows for inspecting and affecting the state of a running DeviceScript program.

0e09030e-6a21-585d-a24a-3610c5b9f1d5.title: DeviceScript Manager
0e09030e-6a21-585d-a24a-3610c5b9f1d5.description:
Allows for deployment and control over DeviceScript virtual machine.

Programs start automatically after device restart or uploading of new program.
You can stop programs until next reset by setting the `running` and `autostart` registers to `false`.

7514ba8c-1934-5a43-9008-8c4b8e790942.title: Jacdac Developer's-tool Electronic module Kit B
7514ba8c-1934-5a43-9008-8c4b8e790942.description:
Dive deep into the forefront of electronic interfacing with the Jacdac Elite Module Suite. Built on the bedrock of Microsoft's avant-garde Jacdac protocol, this suite aggregates an array of meticulously crafted modules, setting the gold standard for next-gen electronic projects.

It Includes:

Jacdac-Power	X1
Jacdac-Haptic Output	X1
Jacdac-Accelerometer	X1
Jacdac-Relay	X1
Jacdac-Env Sensor	X1
Jacdac-RGB Strip	X1
Jacdac-Servo	X1
Jacdac-Ultrasonic	X1
Jacdac-Hub_B	X1
Jacdac Cable  10 cm	X2
Jacdac Cable 35 cm	X2
Jacdac Cable  100 cm	X1

acc8fc99-f95e-5396-b31f-c36acf69ba7a.title: Distance
acc8fc99-f95e-5396-b31f-c36acf69ba7a.description: A sensor that determines the distance of an object without any physical contact involved.

10f339ba-6483-5552-b778-5b490a7c9ee7.title: Jacdac Starter Kit A with Jacdaptor for micro:bit V2

70f30020-e43c-5e14-bd63-68cb9d96ed12.title: DMX
70f30020-e43c-5e14-bd63-68cb9d96ed12.description: A service that can send DMX512-A packets with limited size. This service is designed to allow tinkering with a few DMX devices, but only allows 235 channels. More about DMX at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DMX512.

1e2dc157-b9ad-5899-8a0a-acccef15b371.title: Dot Matrix
1e2dc157-b9ad-5899-8a0a-acccef15b371.description: A rectangular dot matrix display, made of monochrome LEDs or Braille pins.

911437f7-3056-5ab5-8799-2cff01d6717a.title: NanoScript 2040
911437f7-3056-5ab5-8799-2cff01d6717a.description: Elevate your embedded projects with our cutting-edge development board, powered by Raspberry Pi's RP2040 and tailored for DeviceScript. Experience the unmatched synergy of TypeScript in the realm of microcontroller programming, where precision, efficiency, and modern development practices converge.

41ee6183-7a1c-5601-a4f5-45242b858f9c.title: Gamepad
41ee6183-7a1c-5601-a4f5-45242b858f9c.description: A two axis directional gamepad with optional buttons.

3904daf0-0a75-5c9a-8d5c-b64192be1551.title: Newbit Arcade Shield Expansion Board for Micro:bit V2
3904daf0-0a75-5c9a-8d5c-b64192be1551.description: KittenBot Newbit Arcade Shield is an expansion board developed exclusively for Micro:bit V2. It provides Micro:bit V2 the ability not only to be a console, but also to create programmable games. Equipped with the Newbit Arcade Shield, you can use Micro:bit to design games online in MakeCodeArcade, or play games offline, which will broaden your experience of programming with Micro:bit V2.

b4e40075-f62c-5f2a-905e-7019edf3535c.title: GPIO
b4e40075-f62c-5f2a-905e-7019edf3535c.description:
Access to General Purpose Input/Output (GPIO) pins on a board.
The pins are indexed `0 ... num_pins-1`.
The indexing does not correspond to hardware pin names, nor labels on the board (see `get_pin_info` command for that),
and should **not** be exposed to the user.

ab58fde1-5030-5f3a-a4a2-04e567d41c5d.title: Power
ab58fde1-5030-5f3a-a4a2-04e567d41c5d.description: Power module is used to supply high-current JACDAC modules such as servo modules.It can also be used to supply power to the entire JACDAC electronic system.It has overcurrent protection and a maximum output current of 1A.

2c6fc31f-ae10-56d7-9b03-31346ab8a2b3.title: Relay
2c6fc31f-ae10-56d7-9b03-31346ab8a2b3.description:
This relay module is designed for low voltage and low current applications. It's recommended to use a voltage of 5V and a current no greater than 1A.
When using a relay module, it's important to be aware of electrical safety. It's recommended that you use the relay module under adult supervision, especially if you are not familiar with electrical circuits and how to use them safely.

d9517b76-a072-5d5b-be75-f246d9dbf769.title: Heart Rate
d9517b76-a072-5d5b-be75-f246d9dbf769.description:
A sensor approximating the heart rate. 


**Jacdac is NOT suitable for medical devices and should NOT be used in any kind of device to diagnose or treat any medical conditions.**

8c3deeab-0749-5302-88c3-550eb8452732.title: RGB Ring
8c3deeab-0749-5302-88c3-550eb8452732.description: A ring of 8 colored programmable LEDs.

b5127708-8db7-575f-ba92-f55a214f9002.title: RGB Strip
b5127708-8db7-575f-ba92-f55a214f9002.description: RGB Strip module is used to drive WS2812 LED strips. If you're driving a large number of LEDs, such as more than 10, it's recommended to provide additional power to the LED strip to ensure stable and reliable operation.

4f314937-8f9d-5d0f-a1f5-4c4b486d9fe4.title: HID Keyboard
4f314937-8f9d-5d0f-a1f5-4c4b486d9fe4.description:
Control a HID keyboard.

The codes for the key (selectors) is defined in the [HID Keyboard
specification](https://usb.org/sites/default/files/hut1_21.pdf), chapter 10 Keyboard/Keypad Page, page 81.
Modifiers are in page 87.

The device keeps tracks of the key state and is able to clear it all with the clear command.

42148aa2-1d8a-54a6-bd7d-c97c303a677e.title: Servo
42148aa2-1d8a-54a6-bd7d-c97c303a677e.description: Servo module is used to drive standard 3-wire analog servos. It has two output channels and can operate in two different current output modes: 500mA and 1A.

b889c9d1-d6f8-58cb-8c73-e50eb3651b59.title: Humidity
b889c9d1-d6f8-58cb-8c73-e50eb3651b59.description: A sensor measuring humidity of outside environment.

f56b9647-3472-5521-b521-2b859d1fdb5b.title: I2C
f56b9647-3472-5521-b521-2b859d1fdb5b.description:
Inter-Integrated Circuit (I2C, I²C, IIC) serial communication bus lets you communicate with
many sensors and actuators.

7d7020f5-12b2-5c30-b7ea-0dd89ea5512a.title: Ultrasonic Sensor
7d7020f5-12b2-5c30-b7ea-0dd89ea5512a.description: The Ultrasonic Distance Measurement module has a detection range of approximately 3.5 meters.

a154d921-3669-54aa-a5f1-76c0136caaa0.title: Illuminance
a154d921-3669-54aa-a5f1-76c0136caaa0.description:
Detects the amount of light falling onto a given surface area.

Note that this is different from _luminance_, the amount of light that passes through, emits from, or reflects off an object.

c1173a11-c923-57a1-ac94-46d0399d4914.title: ACCESS:bit
c1173a11-c923-57a1-ac94-46d0399d4914.description: The ACCESS:bit is a bolt-on/clip-on board for the BBC microbit that simulates an access barrier.

55014d55-d8d3-5a91-b7e4-89a26b33a7ea.title: Indexed screen
55014d55-d8d3-5a91-b7e4-89a26b33a7ea.description:
A screen with indexed colors from a palette.

This is often run over an SPI connection or directly on the MCU, not regular single-wire Jacdac.

b7d35b72-8a02-556f-a60e-34698d4bad5b.title: Air Quality Board
b7d35b72-8a02-556f-a60e-34698d4bad5b.description: The Kitronik Air Quality Board provides a complete air monitoring and reporting solution for the BBC micro:bit . The wealth of onboard sensors and connection points allow you to collect extensive air quality data that can be stored in onboard memory and displayed on the OLED screen or transferred to a computer for analysis.

26f98c9b-0f9d-5f96-ab38-f150a496f0d6.title: Infrastructure
26f98c9b-0f9d-5f96-ab38-f150a496f0d6.description:
A service that tags a device as purely infrastructure device.


A Jacdac user interface can hide any device that hosts this service.

e429b71f-3fe9-5c0f-930a-cef0a031ed75.title: SERVO:LITE
e429b71f-3fe9-5c0f-930a-cef0a031ed75.description: The Servo:Lite board for the BBC micro:bit is a simple board that allows you to easily connect and control low power servo motors (servo's must be capable of operating at 3.3V) using the BBC micro:bit. It is connected to the micro:bit using five bolts. Connect two servos in standard configuration and it can drive up to 3 servos if the addressable 'ZIP' LEDs aren’t needed.

4ebcebba-eeb5-5715-a5ae-89c7446837ca.title: LED
4ebcebba-eeb5-5715-a5ae-89c7446837ca.description:
A controller for displays of individually controlled RGB LEDs.

For 64 or less LEDs, the service should support the pack the pixels in the pixels register.
Beyond this size, the register should return an empty payload as the amount of data exceeds
the size of a packet. Typically services that use more than 64 LEDs
will run on the same MCU and will maintain the pixels buffer internally.

fb606823-8a7c-5250-b7cb-fa9f2ca72f0f.title: STOP:bit
fb606823-8a7c-5250-b7cb-fa9f2ca72f0f.description: The STOP:bit for the BBC micro:bit is the ultimate upgrade for traffic light/pedestrian crossing projects.

df9d106e-354d-567d-b423-2a5bc379a430.title: LED Single
df9d106e-354d-567d-b423-2a5bc379a430.description: A controller for 1 or more monochrome or RGB LEDs connected in parallel.

a4450b00-8cda-5615-8d75-acea5d9ef5ad.title: Relay Breakout Board
a4450b00-8cda-5615-8d75-acea5d9ef5ad.description:
Keyestudio relay breakout board for micro:bit has integrated a 4-way 5V relay module, fully compatible with micro:bit development board.
It can work only need to insert micro:bit into keyestudio relay shield, then input DC5V voltage on the relay VIN/GND port, pretty simple and convenient.

2c300a04-840b-598b-9643-fb43c8c41e5c.title: LED Strip
2c300a04-840b-598b-9643-fb43c8c41e5c.description: A controller for strips of individually controlled RGB LEDs.

1083fcf9-986c-529f-9e02-fd6ea92d62f2.title: Game:bit Expansion Board
1083fcf9-986c-529f-9e02-fd6ea92d62f2.description: Game:Bit is a brand new product based on Microsoft Arcade games , providing users with different choices for learning micro:bit. Break away from the previous model of using expansion boards and sensors to create projects, and use the method of creating interesting games to stimulate learners' different programming thinking. From how to set the scoring method, character movements, background and music matching, to the judgment of victory and defeat and the ending process, everything in the entire game is decided by the game creator.

bf4dab54-38a5-5c2a-8116-bad40075f2b0.title: Light level
bf4dab54-38a5-5c2a-8116-bad40075f2b0.description: A sensor that measures luminosity level.

98a1021b-f50a-5a36-bc26-3e124e0c29e5.title: Relay
98a1021b-f50a-5a36-bc26-3e124e0c29e5.description:
A switching relay.

The contacts should be labelled `NO` (normally open), `COM` (common), and `NC` (normally closed).
When relay is energized it connects `NO` and `COM`.
When relay is not energized it connects `NC` and `COM`.
Some relays may be missing `NO` or `NC` contacts.
When relay module is not powered, or is in bootloader mode, it is not energized (connects `NC` and `COM`).

e1e6627f-b2a6-5e9e-83ab-a5a97169e97c.title: micro:bit Retro Programming Arcade
e1e6627f-b2a6-5e9e-83ab-a5a97169e97c.description: micro:bit Retro Arcade is a color screen joystick expansion board for micro:bit V2, it contains a TFT 160*128 color screen, 4 directional buttons, two A/B buttons and a reset button. micro:bit Retro Arcade can be used with micro:bit V2 to program games online and play offline on the Microsoft Arcade programming platform. It is a simple and fun way to help children write their own games and understand the mystery behind them. It also supports custom game characters, diverse scenarios and plot design using graphical programming software, making it easy for everyone to achieve fun electronic creations and unlimited game ideas. micro:bit Retro Arcade can also be used as a remote control handle in addition to a game programming learning machine.

9f194d9a-3f91-5ab2-b7ee-ae0a84511592.description:

This typically uses a cryptographical pseudo-random number generator (for example [Fortuna](<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fortuna_(PRNG)>)),
which is periodically re-seeded with entropy coming from some hardware source.

a4a61905-d18a-5228-88b6-76a94efa5d8c.title: USB Bridge
a4a61905-d18a-5228-88b6-76a94efa5d8c.description:
This service is normally not announced or otherwise exposed on the serial bus.
It is used to communicate with a USB-Jacdac bridge at the USB layer.
The host sends broadcast packets to this service to control the link layer.
The device responds with broadcast reports (no-one else does that).
These packets are not forwarded to the UART Jacdac line.

Packets are sent over USB Serial (CDC).
The host shall set the CDC to 1Mbaud 8N1
(even though in some cases the USB interface is connected directly to the MCU and line settings are
ignored).

The CDC line carries both Jacdac frames and serial logging output.
Jacdac frames have valid CRC and are framed by delimeter characters and possibly fragmented.

`0xFE` is used as a framing byte.
Note that bytes `0xF8`-`0xFF` are always invalid UTF-8.
`0xFF` occurs relatively often in Jacdac packets, so is not used for framing.

The following sequences are supported:

* `0xFE 0xF8` - literal 0xFE
* `0xFE 0xF9` - reserved; ignore
* `0xFE 0xFA` - indicates that some serial logs were dropped at this point
* `0xFE 0xFB` - indicates that some Jacdac frames were dropped at this point
* `0xFE 0xFC` - Jacdac frame start
* `0xFE 0xFD` - Jacdac frame end

0xFE followed by any other byte:
* in serial, should be treated as literal 0xFE (and the byte as itself, unless it's 0xFE)
* in frame data, should terminate the current frame fragment,
  and ideally have all data (incl. fragment start) in the current frame fragment treated as serial
